Gareth Isherwood (born 28 November 1988, in Manchester) is a speedway rider from Cadishead, Salford, Greater Manchester. In the 2011 season he rode for Stoke Potters.He has rode for three National league clubs since 2005 in which was his debut season. They are Scunthorpe, Stoke Potters and Buxton Hitmen. In 2008, whilst riding for Buxton, Isherwood won the prestigious Gold Cup award which was awarded to the best rider.